=head1 DESCRIPTION

Used to specify the name of a built-in prompt dataset and optionally,
the Amazon S3 bucket where a custom prompt dataset is saved.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 DatasetLocation => L<Paws::Bedrock::EvaluationDatasetLocation>

For custom prompt datasets, you must specify the location in Amazon S3
where the prompt dataset is saved.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Name => Str

Used to specify supported built-in prompt datasets. Valid values are
C<Builtin.Bold>, C<Builtin.BoolQ>, C<Builtin.NaturalQuestions>,
C<Builtin.Gigaword>, C<Builtin.RealToxicityPrompts>,
C<Builtin.TriviaQA>, C<Builtin.T-Rex>,
C<Builtin.WomensEcommerceClothingReviews> and C<Builtin.Wikitext2>.



